## 1. Executive Summary

MathStudio is a **personal mathematical research library management system** designed to catalog, search, enrich, and interact with a large collection of mathematical PDFs and DjVu files. It combines:

- **AI-powered metadata extraction** (Gemini Vision) for automatic cataloging
- **Multi-strategy hybrid search** (FTS5 + vector embeddings + AI reranking)
- **Knowledge Base**: Flat Term Index for formal theorems and definitions, with "Speaking Name" AI inference and Obsidian sync
- **Note system** supporting handwritten scan transcription and PDF-to-LaTeX conversion
- **External API enrichment** via zbMATH, Crossref, OpenAlex, arXiv, OpenLibrary
- **MCP server** enabling LLM agents (Claude, Gemini) to interact with the library as an Agentic RAG system
- **Bibliography extraction** using Vision LLM for citation graph construction
- **Android E-Ink client** (separate Kotlin project) for mobile reading

The system serves as a "digital mathematical librarian" тАФ ingesting raw PDFs, extracting metadata, classifying by MSC codes, building searchable indexes, and enabling AI-powered research workflows.

