### Key Architectural Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| SQLite with WAL mode | Single-user system; no need for PostgreSQL overhead. WAL enables concurrent reads during writes |
| MCP as HTTP proxy | MCP server calls Flask API via HTTP rather than importing services directly тАФ enables independent deployment |
| Gemini Vision for OCR | Mathematical notation is poorly handled by traditional OCR; Vision LLM preserves LaTeX structure |
| Singleton service instances | Each service module creates a global instance at import time (e.g., `search_service = SearchService()`) |
| Thread-local DB connections | `threading.local()` ensures each thread gets its own SQLite connection |
| Relative paths in DB | Book paths stored relative to `LIBRARY_ROOT` for portability across mounts |

